docs.title: Welcome to Stephanie's test MkDocs website
docs.text:
This is supposed to be versioned at 0.1

deployed only by interactively pushing mike at command line:

mike deploy --push --update-aliases 0.1 latest

docs.title: docs page
docs.text:
this is the first docs page, and it has a relative link to doc2.md. the relative link is doc2.md/#doc2-subsection, so need the full file extension. but it works nicely and I appreciate that. and I have mkdocs serve running in the background right now and the website is live-updating as I save.

I was excited to try out instant previews but it turns out it's only for sponsors starting at $15/month, which, nope :/.

docs.title: doc2 subsection
docs.text:
this is a subsection and I hope the rellink to it in doc1.md works.

sce <- readRDS("SCPCL000000_processed.rds")

I didn't install any kind of code highlighting, but I could have: https://squidfunk.github.io/mkdocs-material/reference/code-blocks/
